{{Infobox music festival | music_festival_name = Metal Open Air | image = | caption = | location = Parque Independência, [[São Luís, Maranhão]], [[Brazil]] | years_active = 2012 | founders = Natanael Jr. | dates = | genre = [[Heavy Metal music|Heavy metal]] | website = }} '''Metal Open Air''' (also known simply as '''MOA''') was an unsuccessful<ref name=UG>{{cite web|title=Disaster Strikes Brazilian Metal Festival|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/general_music_news/disaster_strikes_brazilian_metal_festival.html|publisher=[[Ultimate Guitar Archive]]|accessdate=19 March 2013|date=23 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=exame>{{cite news|title=Mico do ano, festival Metal Open Air é finalmente cancelado|url=http://exame.abril.com.br/estilo-de-vida/entretenimento/noticias/mico-do-ano-festival-metal-open-air-e-finalmente-cancelado/|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=[[Exame (magazine)|Exame]]|date=22 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=terra>{{cite news|last=Louise|first=Aline|title=Metal Open Air é cancelado e empresa organizadora é processada|url=http://musica.terra.com.br/metal-open-air-e-cancelado-e-empresa-organizadora-e-processada,391cbbd670a5a310VgnCLD200000bbcceb0aRCRD.html|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=[[Terra Networks|Terra]]|date=22 April 2012|location=São Luis|language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=g1>{{cite news|title=Procon orienta público do Metal Open Air a exigir ressarcimento|url=http://g1.globo.com/ma/maranhao/noticia/2012/04/procon-orienta-publico-do-metal-open-air-exigir-ressarcimento.html|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=G1|date=22 April 2012|location=Maranhão|language=Portuguese}}</ref> 2012 [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] [[Music festival|festival]]. It took place between 20–22 April, at the Parque Independência, 25&nbsp;km southeast from downtown São Luís, Maranhão, northeastern Brazil.<ref name=rollingstone>{{cite news|last=Rodrigues|first=Stella|title=Primeira edição do Metal Open Air acontecerá em São Luís em abril do ano que vem|url=http://rollingstone.com.br/noticia/primeira-edicao-do-metal-open-air-acontecera-em-sao-luis-em-abril-do-ano-que-vem/|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=''[[Rolling Stone]] Brasil''|date=24 November 2011|language=Portuguese|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111228010608/http://rollingstone.com.br/noticia/primeira-edicao-do-metal-open-air-acontecera-em-sao-luis-em-abril-do-ano-que-vem|archivedate=28 December 2011|df=}}</ref> Due to problems with the payment of artists and the accommodation and security of the audience, the festival was ultimately cancelled on its last day.
== Background and official line-up == Originally, it was supposed to be a Brazilian version of the famous German [[Wacken Open Air]].<ref name=rollingstone/> However, the promoters failed to obtain official permission to use the name, so they decided to switch it for Metal Open Air.<ref name=rollingstone/> From that moment on, several bands, including [[Shaman (Brazilian band)|Shaman]], [[Megadeth]], [[Symphony X]] and [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]],<ref name="vírgula">{{cite news|title=Sem shows nem estrutura, Metal Open Air é cancelado|url=http://virgula.uol.com.br/ver/noticia/festivais-de-musica/2012/04/21/298723-sem-shows-nem-estrutura-metal-open-air-e-cancelado|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=[[Universo Online|Vírgula]]|date=21 April 2012|language=Portuguese}}</ref> started to confirm their performances, though a few have cancelled, including [[Shadowside]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Salzano Jr|first=Costábile|title=Metal Open Air: Shadowside cancela participação no evento|url=http://whiplash.net/materias/news_842/147389-krisiun.html|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=Whiplash.net|date=3 February 2012|language=Portuguese}}</ref> [[Krisiun]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Metal Open Air: Krisiun cancela sua participação no evento|url=http://whiplash.net/materias/news_840/152194-metalopenair.html|accessdate=17 March 2013|newspaper=Whiplash.net|date=12 April 2012|language=Portuguese}}</ref> and [[Volbeat]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Metal Open Air: Volbeat cancela sua participação no evento|url=http://whiplash.net/materias/news_843/146543-metalopenair.html|accessdate=19 March 2013|newspaper=Whiplash.net|date=23 January 2012|language=Portuguese}}</ref> mostly for logistical reasons.
By February/March 2012, the official announced line-up was as follows (act names in '''bold''' are headliners; El Diablo is an entertainment group that prepared rock night parties after every headliner performance):<ref>{{cite news|title=Metal Open Air: anunciada a programação oficial do evento|url=http://whiplash.net/materias/news_842/148537-metalopenair.html|accessdate=19 March 2013|newspaper=Whiplash.net|date=17 February 2012|language=Portuguese}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable" |- !width=33%|Friday, 20 April !width=33%|Saturday, 21 April !width=33%|Sunday, 22 April |- || * [[Semblant]] * [[Ânsia de Vômito]] * [[Drowned (band)|Drowned]] * [[Headhunter D.C.]] * [[Hangar (band)|Hangar]] * [[Almah (band)|Almah]] * [[Orphaned Land]] * [[Torture Squad]] * [[Exciter (band)|Exciter]] * [[Anvil (band)|Anvil]] * [[Destruction (band)|Destruction]] * [[Exodus (band)|Exodus]] * [[Symphony X]] * '''[[Megadeth]]''' * EL DIABLO: Fúria Louca + Fetish Dolls || * [[Terra Prima]] * [[Ácido]] * [[Obskure]] * [[Dark Avenger (band)|Dark Avenger]] * [[Shadowside]] * [[Stress (Brazilian band)|Stress]] * [[Legion of the Damned (band)|Legion of the Damned]] * [[Andre Matos]] * [[Korzus]] * [[U.D.O.]] * [[Grave Digger (band)|Grave Digger]] * [[Blind Guardian]] * [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]] * '''[[Rock and Roll All Stars]]''' * EL DIABLO: Carro Bomba + Fetish Dolls || * [[Expose Your Hate]] * [[Megaherz]] * [[Unearthly (band)|Unearthly]] * [[Attomica]] * [[Motorocker]] * [[Matanza (band)|Matanza]] * [[Otep]] * [[Shaman (Brazilian band)|Shaman]] * [[Ratos de Porão]] * [[Obituary (band)|Obituary]] * [[Dio Disciples]] * [[Fear Factory]] * [[Annihilator (band)|Annihilator]] * [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]] * '''[[Venom (band)|Venom]]''' * EL DIABLO: Baranga + Fetish Dolls |}
The headliners of the second day, the [[Rock and Roll All Stars]], were a [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]] composed of [[Gene Simmons]], [[Joe Elliott]], [[Matt Sorum]], [[Duff McKagan]] , [[Gilby Clarke]], [[Glenn Hughes]], [[Ed Roland]], [[Sebastian Bach]], [[Steve Stevens]], [[Mike Inez]], [[Billy Duffy]] and [[Charlie Sheen]], who was to be the festival's [[master of ceremonies]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Charlie Sheen convida para o Metal Open Air, que ocorre a partir de 20 de abril no Maranhão|url=http://musica.uol.com.br/ultnot/2012/04/09/charlie-sheen-convida-para-o-metal-open-air-que-ocorre-a-partir-de-20-de-abril-no-maranhao.jhtm|publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL Música]]|accessdate=19 March 2013|location=São Paulo|language=Portuguese|date=9 April 2012}}</ref>
== The festival and the cancellations == [[File:Symphony x 2004.tiff|thumb|right|220px|[[Michael Romeo]] (left) and [[Russell Allen]] (right); Symphony X was among the very few bands that managed to make a performance at the festival.]]
Shortly before and even during the festival, several bands cancelled their performances. British thrash band Venom, for example, had their [[Visa (document)|visas]] sent to Africa instead of Brazil by mistake,<ref name=UG/> thus making it impossible for them to take part of MOA and two other South American festivals. [[Hansi Kürsch]], vocalist for German power metal quartet Blind Guardian, stated:<ref>{{cite web|title=Metal Open Air 2012 performance cancelled|url=http://www.blind-guardian.com/2012/04/21/metal-open-air-2012-performance-cancelled/|publisher=Official Blind Guardian website|accessdate=19 March 2013|location=São Luís|date=21 April 2012}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
{{cquote|''In 25 years of our career we [...] have been extremely successful in the avoidance of cancelled shows, so far. This unfortunately comes to a very sad end here in São Luís. Due to massive technical and administrative problems we were forced to cancel tonight's show. As far as we understand it seems to be the local management who has not been able to secure a proper festival environment, anymore. Things are pretty out of hand there. We feel very sorry about this totally unsatisfying situation, but the mistakes made by the local promoter makes an even improvised show impossible. [...] In the future we will be more careful in confirming such festivals.''}}
[[Aquiles Priester]], from Hangar, also cancelled his band's participation, stating:<ref name=exame/>
{{cquote|''We negotiated everything via oral conversation, but we made ourselves very much clear that we needed the total cash before our performance, since we needed to pay our trip to São Luís in our very own bus. We wouldn't accept, by any means, to play without our backline. So far, we were paid with only 25% of the cash to cover all our expenses (fuel, accommodation and food for the band and crew), we needed at least 75%.''}}
Terra Prima's members didn't receive their air tickets to São Luís nor the confirmation of their accommodations in the city.<ref name=exame/>
Symphony X, one of the few bands that managed to take on the stage and perform, posted a note some days later, thanking their fans for the show and criticizing the event's structure:<ref>{{cite web|title=Metal Open Air|url=http://www.symphonyx.com/site/news/metal-open-air/|publisher=Official Symphony X website|accessdate=19 March 2013|date=25 April 2012}}</ref>
{{cquote|''We want to thank the fans for sticking it out on Friday night! We were extremely close to having to cancel the show due to technical reasons and did not know if we would even play for sure until an hour before the set, which had already been delayed two hours. The lack of organization and chaos surrounding the event, which had also been noted by the media, had forced many bands to cancel. This is unfair to the fans in attendance, and unfortunately these fans were robbed of many performances.''}}
[[Dave Mustaine]], from Megadeth, also thanked his fans and regretted the festival's organization:<ref>{{cite web|title=Megadeth Mainman On Brazil's METAL OPEN AIR: 'We Were Playing For The People'|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=172916|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=19 March 2013|date=21 April 2012}}</ref>
{{cquote|''To the fans last night in São Luís, thank you. It's all I can say. One Big Mega Thank You! Yesterday's show in Sao Luis was very challenging, but we did it! [...] I was told a lot of the talent opted out from coming. I was also told the tickets cost $450 [[Brazilian real]] for the three-day weekend, and $250 BRL for just one day. The average person in this area makes $28 BRL a day, so you can do the math. [...] We were playing, no matter what. We weren't playing for the promoter anymore; we were playing for the people!''}}
[[Ricardo Confessori]], drummer for [[Shaman]], publicly contested Anthrax guitarist [[Scott Ian]] for canceling the band's performance at the festival, accusing him of not giving a good excuse for the fans, to which Ian replied that the problem was "the whole terrible organization. We never want to cancel but they made it impossible."<ref>[https://twitter.com/Scott_Ian/status/193877446603448320 Confessori's and Ian's discussion] at [[Twitter]].</ref>
In the end, a total of 30 of the 47 invited bands cancelled their performances due to the severe logistical, structural and financial problems regarding the festival.<ref name=UG/> As for the fans, some had to camp inside [[stable]]s, with almost no electricity, lack of places to buy food, beverage and hygiene products and only one public toilet.<ref>{{cite web|last=Freire|first=Pedro Henrique|title=Estábulos para cavalos viram área de camping para o público|url=http://www.oimparcial.com.br/app/noticia/especiais/metal-open-air/2012/04/20/interna_metal,113830/estabulos-para-cavalos-viram-area-de-camping-para-o-publico.shtml|publisher=O Imparcial|accessdate=19 March 2013|location=São Luís|language=Portuguese|date=20 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524014607/http://www.oimparcial.com.br/app/noticia/especiais/metal-open-air/2012/04/20/interna_metal,113830/estabulos-para-cavalos-viram-area-de-camping-para-o-publico.shtml#|archive-date=2013-05-24|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Barbosa|first=Alex|title= Festival de heavy metal desaponta fãs em São Luís do Maranhão|url=http://g1.globo.com/jornal-nacional/videos/t/edicoes/v/festival-de-heavy-metal-desaponta-fas-em-sao-luis-do-maranhao/1914720/|publisher=[[Jornal Nacional]]|accessdate=19 March 2013|location=São Luís|language=Portuguese|date=21 April 2012}}</ref>
== Aftermath == Soon after MOA was cancelled, both companies responsible for the festival (Negri Concerts and Lamparina Filmes e Produções) accused each other of breaking contractual rules.<ref name=negrivslamparina>{{cite web|last=Louise|first=Aline|title=Produtoras do Metal Open Air trocam acusações em cartas abertas|url=http://musica.terra.com.br/produtoras-do-metal-open-air-trocam-acusacoes-em-cartas-abertas,fa3cbbd670a5a310VgnCLD200000bbcceb0aRCRD.html|publisher=Terra|accessdate=19 March 2013|location=São Luís|language=Portuguese|date=24 March 2013}}</ref>
